## 2. When to Use Which Block

### 2.1 Content blocks

```
What kind of content?
  ├─ Formatted prose, lists, code samples → markdown
  ├─ Raw HTML (migration only)             → html         (avoid for new content)
  ├─ Image                                 → image        (require alt text)
  └─ Embedded video                        → video        (YouTube or native)
```

### 2.2 Interactive vs Multistep vs Guided

```
How does the user perform the action?
  ├─ Single click / fill / navigate                 → interactive
  ├─ Two+ actions, the SYSTEM performs them auto    → multistep
  ├─ Two+ actions, the USER performs them manually  → guided
  │   (also required when CSS :hover must trigger,
  │    or when the target is virtualised — lazyRender)
  └─ One step that wraps a multistep                → BAD — multistep singleton
```

### 2.3 Structural blocks

```
Need to group steps?                  → section (unique kebab-case id)
Branch on runtime state?              → conditional
  ├─ display: "inline"  → prose with hidden/shown branches
  └─ display: "section" → each branch gets its own "Do" button + title
Add AI customization?                 → assistantEnabled on the block (preferred),
                                        or assistant wrapper (legacy format)
Choose-your-own-adventure decision    → grot-guide  (block editor only — CLI-excluded)
```

### 2.4 Assessment blocks

```
Knowledge check?                       → quiz
  ├─ Must answer correctly to advance  → completionMode: "correct-only"
  └─ Reveal answer after N tries       → completionMode: "max-attempts", maxAttempts: N
Capture user input as a variable?      → input
  ├─ Free text                          → inputType: "text"
  ├─ Checkbox                           → inputType: "boolean"
  └─ Datasource picker                  → inputType: "datasource", datasourceFilter: "..."
```

### 2.5 Specialized blocks

```
Insert code into a Monaco editor?     → code-block (not formfill)
Shell command demo?                   → terminal           (needs is-terminal-active)
Open the terminal session itself?     → terminal-connect   (place before terminal blocks)
Choose-your-own-adventure tree?       → grot-guide         (block editor, not CLI)
```

