## 3. When to Use Which Action

### 3.1 Click, fill, navigate, hover, noop, popout

```
What does the step do?
  ├─ Click a button by visible text   → action: "button",    reftarget: "Save & test"
  ├─ Click anything else (CSS)        → action: "highlight", reftarget: "<selector>"
  ├─ Fill a field                     → action: "formfill",  reftarget + targetvalue
  ├─ Change page                      → action: "navigate",  reftarget: "/path"
  │   └─ Open another guide after     → add openGuide: "bundled:<id>"
  ├─ Reveal :hover-hidden UI          → action: "hover"      (use guided for real :hover)
  ├─ Informational pause              → action: "noop"       (reftarget optional)
  └─ Toggle docs panel position       → action: "popout"     (targetvalue required:
                                                              "sidebar" | "floating")
```

### 3.2 `popout` vs `navigate`

`popout` operates on the docs panel; `navigate` operates on the Grafana page. They are unrelated — `popout` does not change the URL.

### 3.3 `openGuide` (cross-guide handoff)

Prefer the `openGuide` field on a `navigate` interactive block over appending `?doc=` to the URL. The query-string form is back-compat only.

```json
{ "action": "navigate", "reftarget": "/connections/datasources/new",
  "openGuide": "bundled:add-prometheus-datasource" }
```

### 3.4 `formfill` regex patterns

When `validateInput: true`, `targetvalue` is regex-aware:

| Pattern | Matches |
|---------|---------|
| `prometheus` | exact string |
| `^https?://` | strings starting with `http://` or `https://` |
| `monitoring$` | strings ending with `monitoring` |
| `/^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$/i` | full regex with flags |

Use `validateInput: false` (default) when you want to accept any non-empty value.

### 3.5 Lazy-rendered targets

`lazyRender` lives on the **step**, not on the block. Always wrap a lazy-rendered target in a `guided` block — user-paced detection avoids racing the scroll.

```json
{ "action": "button", "reftarget": "...", "lazyRender": true,
  "scrollContainer": "div[data-testid='dashboards-table'] .scrollbar-view" }
```

