## 4. When to Use Which Requirement

```
Element on the page?
  ├─ Nav menu item                      → "navmenu-open"
  ├─ Existing element                   → "exists-reftarget" (include for selector-targeting steps)
  └─ All form fields filled correctly   → "form-valid"

User location?
  └─ On a specific page                 → "on-page:/path"

User identity / permissions?
  ├─ Authenticated                      → "is-logged-in"
  ├─ Editor or higher                   → "is-editor"
  ├─ Grafana admin                      → "is-admin"
  ├─ Specific org role                  → "has-role:<role>"
  └─ Specific permission                → "has-permission:<perm>"  (most specific — wins)

Resources?
  ├─ At least one data source           → "has-datasources"
  ├─ Data source exists (by name/type)  → "has-datasource:<name>"        (no connectivity)
  ├─ Data source exists AND tested      → "datasource-configured:<name>" (slower)
  ├─ Plugin installed                   → "has-plugin:<id>"              (may be disabled)
  ├─ Plugin enabled                     → "plugin-enabled:<id>"
  ├─ Any dashboard                      → "dashboard-exists"
  └─ Specific dashboard by title        → "has-dashboard-named:<title>"

User-collected variables?
  └─ Variable matches expected value    → "var-<name>:<value>"

Environment?
  ├─ Grafana version ≥ X                → "min-version:<x.y.z>"
  ├─ Cloud / OSS / Play                 → "in-environment:<env>"
  └─ Feature flag enabled               → "has-feature:<toggle>"

Rendering context?
  └─ Pathfinder app vs website          → "renderer:pathfinder" | "renderer:website"

Flow / order?
  ├─ Previous section finished          → "section-completed:<id>"
  └─ Terminal session active            → "is-terminal-active"
```

> `exists-reftarget` is the standard requirement for selector-targeting steps — include it in `requirements` for any block or step with a `reftarget`.

