## 5. When to Use Which Objective

Objectives use the same vocabulary as requirements but their behavior is different.

| | Requirement | Objective |
|---|------------|-----------|
| Failure | Step is disabled with "Fix this" UI | Step auto-completes |
| Use for | Preconditions the user must meet | Outcomes the user has already achieved |
| Composition | All must pass | All must pass (auto-complete is all-or-nothing) |

```
Skip when already done?
  ├─ Data source already configured     → "objectives": ["has-datasource:prometheus"]
  ├─ Plugin already installed           → "objectives": ["plugin-enabled:<id>"]
  ├─ Already on target page             → "objectives": ["on-page:/dashboards"]
  └─ Dashboard already created          → "objectives": ["has-dashboard-named:My Dashboard"]
```

Section-level objectives bubble to all child steps: if the section's objectives are met, the whole section is marked complete.

